Level 58 is the 59<sup>th</sup> level of the Backrooms.

==Description==
{{Blurimage|file=Level58-1.png|caption=An image of '''Level 58'''.}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level58-3.png|caption=Another image of '''Level 58'''.}}
Level 58 is a building resembling an old shopping mall that seems to go on forever. The level is constantly changing due to its non-Euclidean geometry, and it is possible for one to move in a straight line and return to the point where they were, or suddenly end up in a completely different place. Despite these characteristics, the level is considered quite safe and contains a large number of colonies, including many undocumented groups. The floor of the building is made of brown square tiles and the walls are covered with smooth white plaster. Most parts of the level are completely empty and occasionally trash bins or vending machines can be found. The building is illuminated by LED ceiling lights and is quite bright [[#Files|most of the time]].

The design of the structure is similar to that of a conventional 1980s retail mall, with several tweaks. Corridors connecting to random chambers or fully dead-end halls, uncomfortably cramped areas, and looping, seemingly infinite corridors are quite common throughout the level. In addition, passages blocked by an invisible barrier and corridors leading to [[The Void]] are also common.

Some parts of the level may have windows showing the outside. It is not possible to damage these windows in any way and climb out. As visible through the windows, the outside of the level consists of empty asphalt roads in empty plains. Although these roads are mostly empty, occasionally completely empty cars with no driver can be seen passing quite fast on these roads. Observations of the sky have shown that time is at least several times slower in the level than in [[The Frontrooms]]. Furthermore, the day is much longer in the level than the night, and it is quite rare to experience the level during the night.

Passing through doors that appear to lead out of the building will take one to another mall building that is nearly identical to the one from which one exited. Returning via these doors may take one back to the same mall or to an entirely different building. On average, each mall building has 7 to 10 floors. Even though all of these floors are almost identical, it has been observed that time bends as the floors change and that the higher one goes, the closer the time of day is to night and the lower one goes, the closer it is to noon.

The majority of the shopping center's stores are practically empty, with only a few vending machines, garbage bins, and empty buckets. However, some stores may continue to operate. Many of these stores are controlled by the [[B.W.O.]] or the '''Level 58 Clan''', however some may be stocked with resources even if they are not owned by any group. These stores are probably the most ideal option for a base, other than joining a colony. The resources inside are generally safe to consume, however occasionally harmful products like expired [[Object 1|Almond Water]] might be found.

Random doors mounted on walls may be found within the level. Some of these doors are unlocked while others are locked, and the locked ones cannot be opened by muscle power or tools of any kind. Unlocked doors will usually open to another random part of the level, but some may open directly to [[The Void]] or another level. It is not recommended to no-clip at this level, as the chance of falling into [[The Void]] is extremely high. According to a [[B.W.O.]] researcher, three of his friends were suddenly lost at the level, and it is likely that they no-clipped and fell into [[The Void]]. In addition, hazardous substances such as broken glass, [[Object 33|Memory Flame]] drops, etc. may be found on the floor. There also may be boxes scattered on the ground around the level. These boxes are mostly completely empty, however, the ones that aren't empty are often filled with harmful substances such as [[Object 33|Memory Flame]].

Throughout the level, a calm, quiet music can be heard playing from the building's loudspeakers. This music is often relaxing for the wanderers and, [[#Files|with one exception]], it plays non-stop at all times. In addition, The wanderers at the level have reported hearing strange whispers or footsteps as the time progressed and that these sounds increased as time went on. This is thought to be a psychological effect of the level on the wanderers. Experts recommend drinking [[Object 1|Almond Water]] once these noises start to appear. If the noises do not decrease, it is advisable just to ignore them completely and focus on the objective.
<br style="clear: both" />
==Entities==
Level 58 contains mostly only non-dangerous entities, such as harmless [[Entity 9|Facelings]], however, it is possible to encounter dangerous entities such as [[Entity 3|Smilers]] on very rare occasions. While there is a risk of encountering dangerous entities such as these, they are considerably slower than normal in this level, so they do not pose much of a threat.
==Colonies and Outposts==
There are three colonies that have been documented by the [[B.W.O.]] in the level so far.
===Base Unus ([[B.W.O.|<span style="color: #454987;">B.W.O.</span>]])===
*Established by the discoverer of the level, [[Jerry M. Sercher]] and his team in a sheltered area of the level, it covers a large part of the level and has a large number of bunkers throughout the level.
*At one point during the base's operation, after [[#Files|an incident]], it was attacked and destroyed, but was rebuilt a few months later.
*Each base owned by the [[B.W.O.]] throughout the level is managed by an administrator and two guards selected by the group.
*They are open to helping lost wanderers and welcoming new members, and the members they recruit will usually be a researcher or explorer working in one of the bases in the level.
*Each base has roughly 15 researchers who manage [[B.W.O.]]'s database.
===Level 58 Clan===
*They do not have a fixed settlement on the level, but can often be seen wandering around the level in groups.
*They make their living by robbing the wanderers on the level.
*They do not welcome new members into their group.
*Following an altercation with a [[B.W.O.]] researcher in the level at the time, a small-scale war broke out between them, which resulted in the destruction of several [[B.W.O.]] bases in the level and the death of many members of the Level 58 Clan, resulting in no clear winner.
===Backroom Residents===
*Quite neutral and not involved in any ongoing conflict at the level.
*They live in small shelters around the level and rely on the resources of the level for their survival.
*It is estimated to consist of 40-60 members.
==Files==
{{Collapse|initial=<span style="color: #a79c8b">>'''The Outage'''</span>|final=<span style="color: #a79c8b"><'''The Outage'''</span>|body=
{{Blurbackground|file=Black-Screen.png}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level58TheOutage.png|caption=An image of '''The Outage'''.}}
At random times throughout the level, the entire power of the level can be suddenly cut off. The entire level will go dark and this event is called '''The Outage'''. During the event, all but the most protected places, such as [[B.W.O.]] bases, will be completely overrun with malevolent entities, and they will be much faster than they normally are in this level. Survival during this event is extremely difficult unless one brings a flashlight or hides in a shelter. The entities will strangely try to escape the light and head for the darkness, so having a flashlight is highly recommended. People who experienced The Outage reported hearing a loud siren blaring from the mall's speakers while the event was in progress. '''The Outage''' does not happen often, so it is possible to move through the level without ever seeing this event.

The first sighting of the event was about two months after the discovery of the level. The level was plunged into darkness without any warning and most of the [[B.W.O.]] researchers and some of the wanderers who roamed the level, not knowing what to do, passed away. The survivors described the incident as "The level suddenly became dark, we realized that it was no longer safe." Following this incident, [[B.W.O.]] bases on the level were organized to be safe from this attack.

A photographer who survived '''The Outage''' described his experiences.

{{Fullscreen|show=> Open Document|hide=> Close Document|padding=2rem 15%|number=1|content=
