<div style="background-position-x: 50%; background-size: 100% 200%; background-repeat: no-repeat; position: fixed; width: 100vw; height: 100vh; z-index: 2; opacity: 0.8; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); animation: sillyanim2 3s infinite alternate;"></div>

<div style="position: relative; display: flex; justify-content: center; width: 100%; margin-top: 100px; overflow: hidden; z-index: 3;">
<div style="width: 80%; text-align: center; color: #f1f3fc; font-family: VT323; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: 2px; text-shadow: 1px 1px 5px #670000; font-weight: bold;">

<div style="font-size: 35px; opacity: 1; letter-spacing: 5px"><span style="font-family: Nunito">File #1</span><div style="display: inline-block; animation: sillyanim 0.75s infinite alternate">:</div> <span style="font-family: Nunito">The Outage</span></div>
<br><br>
<div class="text">
"At random times throughout the level, the entire power of the level can be suddenly cut off. The entire level will go dark and this event is called '''The Outage'''."
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 0.25s;">

</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 0.50s;">
I had read this article before I entered the level, but I didn't think much of it because I knew that the odds were quite rare. When I entered the level, I found myself lying on the square tiled floor. I stood up and looked around me. High ceilings, stairs, yellow railings, windows and white walls covered the building. I went up the stairs and took a few pictures of the scene. My intention was to take a few pictures of the level and then leave anyway.
</div>
<div class="sillyimages" style="display: flex; justify-content: center; height: 600px; width: 100%; opacity: 0.75; margin-top: 20px;">
[[File:Level58-1.png|left|link=]]
[[File:Level58-4.png|right|link=]]
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 1s;">
I wandered around the level a bit more, looking for beautiful views to take pictures. After a while I realized that I was back in the same place, although I didn't understand how it happened. Anyway, I kept going for a while and I encountered three wanderers, and when I greeted them I realized the mistake I had made because they started walking towards me with dangerous looks. From the article I had read, I assumed that they were the Level 58 Clan. One of them, who seemed to be the leader of the group, told me to give them what I was holding, so I told them that I was not going to harm them and to let me go. Of course they refused and pulled out their weapons. Two of them had a stick and one had a knife.
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 1.25s;">
At that very moment, the music playing from the speakers suddenly stopped.
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 1.50s;">
All the light sources on the level began to shake, making sizzling noises, and soon all of them suddenly stopped giving light. There was total darkness everywhere. I remember the Level 58 Clan members I encountered running away cursing, and I froze. What was I going to do? I was probably going to die here, but I still had to look for a place to hide. By the way, I knew that if I didn't start running now, the Hound behind me would tear me apart, so I took quick action. The sirens blaring from the loudspeakers were ringing in my ears. I ran through doors and down corridors, not knowing what I was doing. Soon I woke up in what looked like a bunker. It was a BWO base. I must have blacked out.
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 1.75s;">
I told them what had happened to me, and they suggested that I write an entry about my experience. So that's what I'm writing right now in the aftermath of this event. I'm in a safe BWO base, resting. 
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 2s;">
I am scared.
</div>
